📈 Want more options strategies? Subscribe here: https://www.youtube.com/@YouDomoLLC 💬 Question of the Day: Which stock are you currently selling calls against? Let me know in the comments!

What are Covered Calls?
A covered call is a popular options strategy used to generate extra income from stocks you already own. It’s essentially a "rent-a-stock" strategy where you get paid upfront in exchange for capping your potential upside.

How it Works:
The Setup: You must own at least 100 shares of a stock (this is your "cover").

The Trade: You sell (write) a call option against those shares.

The Payoff: You immediately collect a cash payment called a premium.

The Outcome:

If the stock stays below the strike price: You keep your shares AND the premium. You can then sell another call to generate more income.

If the stock rises above the strike price: You are obligated to sell your shares at that price. You keep the premium and any gains up to the strike, but you miss out on any "moonshot" rallies.

You're sitting at your desk on a Tuesday, wondering "How much longer do I have to do this?" Here's what nobody tells you: almost everyone is obsessed with the wrong number. We chase net worth, but what actually buys freedom is cash flow—real dollars hitting your account every single month.
There are three specific passive income milestones that fundamentally change your life. Not in theory. Right now. Today. And most people quit right before they hit the first one.
🎯 What You'll Learn:

Why $1,000/month is the most underestimated milestone in personal finance
The exact moment passive income stopped being theory and became real for me
Why $3,500/month is the "toxic job shield" that gives you true leverage
How $8,300/month creates full decoupling of time and money
The brutal math: how much you actually need invested for each milestone
Why the first $1,000/month takes HALF the effort of the entire journey
The critical move that separates people who stay stuck from people who accelerate
Why most people quit at $500/month (and how close they actually were)

💰 The Three Milestones:
Milestone #1: $1,000/month ($12,000/year)

Requires ~$300,000 invested (using 4% rule) OR sweat equity assets
This is PROOF—the moment your brain rewires
Covers groceries, utilities, car repairs without panic
Timeline: 9-10 years investing $1,000/month at 8% returns

Milestone #2: $3,500/month ($42,000/year)

Requires ~$1 million invested OR $600K-$800K in rental properties
This is SURVIVAL—covers housing, food, transportation
The toxic job shield: you can walk away from bad situations
Timeline: 15-20 years for most people

Milestone #3: $8,300/month ($100,000/year)

Requires ~$2-$2.5 million invested
This is ABUNDANCE—full financial independence
Six-figure income while you sleep, travel, or do nothing
Timeline: 20-30 years for most disciplined investors

📊 The Uncomfortable Truth:
The difference between milestone 2 and 3 is luxury. The difference between milestone 1 and 2 is SURVIVAL. That's why obsessing over the final number too early is a mistake.
You don't need $2 million to change your life. You need $1,000/month to prove the concept. You need $3,500/month to escape the trap. Everything after that is just icing.
🔥 Why Most People Quit:
Passive income isn't linear—it's exponential. The first $1,000/month consumes HALF the total effort of the entire journey. You're learning skills, building systems, making mistakes, creating infrastructure.
That's why people quit at $400 or $500/month. They think "Three years and I'm making $450/month? Screw this." But they don't realize how close they were. Once the foundation exists, scaling becomes dramatically easier.
💡 The Only Question That Matters:
Where are you right now?

At zero, trying to figure out which path to take?
Stuck around $500, wondering if it's worth continuing?
Already crossed $1,000 and felt the shift?

Wherever you are, you're not alone. The math works. It always has. The only variable is whether you stay long enough to let it compound.

First, let's talk about why digital products and courses are such powerful tools for generating passive income. The beauty of digital products is that you create them once and sell them over and over again. Unlike physical products, there's no inventory to manage, no shipping, and your profit margins are much higher. Whether you're looking to supplement your current income or replace it entirely, digital products can help you achieve your goals.

Method 1 - Creating and Selling E-books
Number one on our list is creating and selling e-books. E-books are a fantastic way to share your expertise on any subject you're passionate about. Platforms like Amazon Kindle Direct Publishing (KDP) make it incredibly easy to publish and sell your e-book to a global audience.

When writing an e-book, focus on solving a specific problem or addressing a particular need within your niche. Do your research, provide valuable insights, and make your content engaging. Once your e-book is published, you can use social media, email marketing, and SEO to drive traffic to your sales page.

Method 2 - Developing Online Courses
The second method is developing online courses. Platforms like Udemy, Teachable, and Coursera have made it easier than ever to create and sell your own online courses. If you have in-depth knowledge of a particular subject or skill, why not teach others and get paid for it?
Start by outlining your course curriculum, breaking it down into manageable modules. Use a mix of video lessons, quizzes, and downloadable resources to keep your students engaged. Remember, the more value you provide, the more likely your students are to recommend your course to others.

Method 3 - Selling Printables and Digital Downloads
The third method is selling printables and digital downloads. This can include anything from planners and calendars to design templates and worksheets. Websites like Etsy and Gumroad are perfect for selling these types of products.

The key to success with printables is creating high-quality, visually appealing products that people will find useful. Consider trends in your niche and design products that meet those needs. You can even bundle multiple items together to increase your sales.

Method 4 - Membership Sites and Subscription Services
Next up, we have membership sites and subscription services. If you have a wealth of content or offer ongoing value, a membership site can be a lucrative option. Platforms like Kartra and Kajabi allow you to charge a monthly fee for access to exclusive content, community forums, and more.

To keep your members engaged and subscribed, consistently provide fresh content and interact with your community. This could include live Q&A sessions, exclusive webinars, and downloadable resources. The goal is to create a sense of belonging and value that keeps your members coming back month after month.

Method 5 - Licensing Your Content
Finally, method number five is licensing your content. This involves allowing others to use your digital products, such as e-books, courses, or software, in exchange for a licensing fee. It's a great way to earn passive income from content you've already created.

Reach out to businesses, educational institutions, or other content creators who might benefit from your materials. Negotiate a licensing agreement that allows them to use your content while you earn a recurring fee. It's a win-win situation for everyone involved.
